I tried to kite in Ill Omen got 2 sarnacs with Bonds of Force and started throwing AE's and backing up. Bear in mind I'm level 30. But I could use any tips you can throw out. Am I doing it right or is there a better place to. Also any instruction as to what spell are used or should be used would be great. Thanks<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uspankda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spankda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/1/01 9:24:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some help with Kiting</span><hr size=1> Sounds like what you're doing is correct.  You'll be more efficient at 34 with Circle of Force. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyofallien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>yofallien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/2/01 4:35:38 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some help with Kiting</span><hr size=1> As a suggestion, when you first start kiting, single kite mobs.  A good indicator of a quad mob is the mana left over from a single kite.  Any time I'm trying a new kiting ground, I try a single first.  Gives you an idea of their hp's and their resists.  When you single kite one, use your most efficient nuke.  Look at the mana you used.  If you are below 2/3rds mana.  I don't suggest multiple kites.  I know some people that will go to the last bub and then still consider the mobs ok to quad kite but I like a little more cushion than that.  <br>
<br>
After you have taken out the mob calc up his HP's by adding up the damage you did. Then look at your AE's.  Pick an AE that you can cast enough times to do the same amount of damage and voila, you are in business.  <br>
<br>
i.e.  Kiting a single sarnak using inferno shock.  The mob took 5 nukes to burn.  You had 1.5 bub of mana left.  Then look at a single pulse of an AE.  Using your preferred AE can you get enough damage with the mana you have against a single mob?   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umithranielshadowcastre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mithraniel Shadowcastre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/2/01 8:44:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some help with Kiting</span><hr size=1> Ok I see what your saying yo thanks. What I have been doing is using a combination of Bonds of Force and then using Shock Spiral or another like Colomn of lightning. I'll try what you suggested. Thanks<br>
Any good hunting grounds for a level 30 wizard? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvoltaeus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Voltaeus</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/3/01 7:26:00 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.onewingedangel.com/magnificent/twelve/volt.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some help with Kiting</span><hr size=1> Solo a spire in SK near PAW ent.  You can even multiple kite there. <p>Voltaeus Visionseeker<BR>
Wizard of the 56th Circle<BR>
The Twelve of Never<BR>
<i>Innoruuk Server</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umithrull.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mithrull</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/4/01 3:14:45 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some help with Kiting</span><hr size=1> I noticed you used the phrase &quot;backing up&quot; in your post. That concerns me. Are you actually walking backwards away from the mob?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/6/01 12:06:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need some help with Kiting</span><hr size=1> The spires in SK are awesome at your level - that's what I'm doing.  Or the Aviaks - pull an avo and a harrier.  If you can get a Staff of Temporate Flux it will make your life easier - manaless pulls, and distance gauging (can we beat the SoTF topic to death or what?).  I've tried snow cougars in iceclad, but they're so many it's tough to get the right number, and not get adds part-way through the kite. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson
